article.description: Alexis Yetna registered 11 points as South Florida beat Loyola Marymount 56-47 in the semifinals of the College Basketball Invitational on Thursday night.
article.headline: Yetna carries South Florida over Loyola Marymount 56-47
article.linkText: Yetna carries South Florida over Loyola Marymount 56-47
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- Alexis Yetna registered 11 points as South Florida beat Loyola Marymount 56-47 in the semifinals of the College Basketball Invitational on Thursday night. David Collins had 11 points for South Florida (22-13). Neither team was able to get much going offensively in the first half, heading to the locker room at the half tied at 22-22. South Florida outscored Loyola Marymount (22-12) by a margin of 34-25 in the second half to earn the victory. The Bulls' 22 first-half points were a season low for the team. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
